name: NPR
text:
The new HBO film "Coastal Elites" is an explosion of emotion about life in 2020, told in five monologues filmed during quarantine. Our critic says not all of the parts work well — but it's worth a watch for the ones that do.
https://t.co/ro0NPVlgW4

name: NPR
text:
Opinion: @nprscottsimon recounts what life in California — once the stuff of dreams — has become for too many residents, as wildfires, mudslides, earthquakes seem to happen with increasing frequency.  
 https://t.co/R3qkHc9zO8

name: NPR
text:
How was the richest country in the world laid low by a virus only nanometers in size? 

The Atlantic’s @edyong209 tells @nprcodeswitch it’s due to the inequities that have been with us all along. https://t.co/3w1JjcWiT9

name: NPR
text:
Tyra Banks has spent years teaching aspiring models to strut their stuff on the catwalk ... but how much does she know about walking dogs? 

@waitwait decided to find out. https://t.co/L6PJCkfoGi

name: NPR
text: In Shannon Hale's new novel, a former child actor — who's finding her teen years challenging after a failed audition — discovers that she can physically enter books and become part of their stories. https://t.co/QpbMa3J3pd

name: NPR
text:
Lauren Eylise impressed the Tiny Desk Contest judges with "Peaks and Valleys," her original song about the struggles that make us who we are.

"We need the sunshine and the rain to grow," she says. "I think that song is where I find a lot of strength."
https://t.co/K0N5eOMcWS

name: NPR
text: Currently millions of American are struggling to pay rent, the risk of widespread homelessness is very real. In this episode, @nprlifekit explains how to qualify for the new eviction moratorium and what to know if you can't pay your rent. https://t.co/yCsX96HY9x

name: NPR
text:
Kevin Parker brings his "Tame Impala Soundsystem" to life from a Tiny Desk in Australia.
https://t.co/g2539QdCmy
